{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftPy"}],"role":"collectionGroup","roleHeading":"API Collection","title":"Creating a Module"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftpy\/creatingmodules"]}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A module is the unit Python code imports to reach your Swift code. The usual building block is a Swift class exposed with the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/Scriptable(_:base:convertsToSnakeCase:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" macro, which you then register in a module by name with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/PyBind\/module(_:block:)","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The module is created lazily the first time it is imported, so registering it is cheap — nothing runs until Python actually needs it. Register your modules once during start up, before any script that imports them runs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Expose-a-Swift-class","text":"Expose a Swift class","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apply the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/Scriptable(_:base:convertsToSnakeCase:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" macro to a class to make it usable from Python. The macro conforms the type to ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/PythonBindable"},{"type":"text","text":" and exposes its initializer, properties, and methods. Names are converted to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"snake_case"},{"type":"text","text":" to match Python conventions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@Scriptable","final class Counter {","    var count: Int = 0","","    init() {}","","    func increment(by amount: Int) {","        count += amount","    }","}"]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Register the module","anchor":"Register-the-module"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/PyBind\/module(_:block:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" with the name Python will import and register the type with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/PyModule\/class(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (or several at once with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/PyModule\/classes(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["PyBind.module(\"game\") { module in","    module.class(Counter.self)","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once registered, the class can be imported and used from Python. Notice "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"increment(by:)"},{"type":"text","text":" is exposed as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"increment"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"python","type":"codeListing","code":["from game import Counter","","counter = Counter()","counter.increment(5)","print(counter.count)   # 5"]},{"text":"Add a function","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Add-a-function"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Modules can also expose standalone functions. Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/PyModule\/def(_:docstring:function:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" with a signature written in Python syntax, including type annotations; an optional docstring shows up in Python’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"help()"},{"type":"text","text":". Inside the body, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PyBind\/function(_:_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" bridges the arguments to Swift types and converts your return value back to Python:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["PyBind.module(\"greetings\") { module in","    module.def(","        \"hello(name: str) -> str\",","        docstring: \"Returns a greeting for the given name.\"","    ) { argc, argv in","        PyBind.function(argc, argv) { (name: String) in","            \"Hello, \\(name)!\"","        }","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The function is then available on the module:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"python","type":"codeListing","code":["import greetings","","print(greetings.hello(\"SwiftPy\"))   # Hello, SwiftPy!"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Functions can be asynchronous too — return an awaitable from an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"async"},{"text":" closure and Python can ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"await"},{"text":" it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy"]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/Scriptable(_:base:convertsToSnakeCase:)","doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/PythonBindable","doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/PyBind","doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/WorkingWithPyObjects"],"anchor":"Related","title":"Related"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Expose Swift types and functions to Python by registering your own module.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/tutorials\/SwiftPyTutorials","doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/WorkingWithPyObjects","doc:\/\/swiftpy.SwiftPy\/documentation\/SwiftPy\/Interpreter"],"anchor":"Essentials","generated":true}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"ur